Dialogue: 0,00:00:16.27,00:00:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbles ]
Dialogue: 0,00:00:20.31,00:00:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:03:12.07,00:03:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Whirring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:03:15.28,00:03:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Stops ] \N[ Shouting ] \NSee how it's done?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:18.32,00:03:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think I got \Nthe hang of it. \NYou better.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:22.41,00:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss'll chew my head off \Nif these cores get messed up. \NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:41.64,00:03:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're at 26 feet.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:43.89,00:03:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You let Jason \Noperate the drill?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:46.14,00:03:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he can \Nhandle it.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:11.54,00:04:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Slows, Stops ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:15.96,00:04:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crunching ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:18.63,00:04:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cracking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:38.74,00:04:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do \Nanything!
Dialogue: 0,00:04:46.79,00:04:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme your hand! \NLet go of the drill!
Dialogue: 0,00:04:57.55,00:05:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it, Jack! \NIt's too late!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:13.31,00:05:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not \Ngonna make it!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:24.49,00:05:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:37.42,00:05:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack! \NGimme your hand!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:40.21,00:05:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:43.26,00:05:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:45.22,00:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:48.85,00:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking? \N[ Sighs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:52.23,00:05:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's happening? \N- The whole damn shelf \Nis breaking off!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:56.86,00:05:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's \Nwhat's happening!
Dialogue: 0,00:06:02.94,00:06:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cracking, Rumbling Continue ]
Dialogue: 0,00:06:17.00,00:06:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NWhat we have found \Nlocked in these ice cores...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:19.38,00:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is evidence of a cataclysmic \Nclimate shift,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:21.67,00:06:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which occurred around \N10,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:24.22,00:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The concentration of these \Nnatural greenhouse gases \Nin the ice cores...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:28.60,00:06:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,indicates that runaway warming \Npushed the planet \Ninto an ice age...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:31.89,00:06:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which lasted two centuries.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:34.27,00:06:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Speaking \NForeign Language ] \NI'm confused.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:37.73,00:06:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were talking \Nabout global warming, \Nnot an ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:42.19,00:06:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is a paradox, \Nbut global warming can trigger \Na cooling trend.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:46.57,00:06:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:48.74,00:06:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The northern hemisphere \Nowes its temperate climate \Nto the North Atlantic current.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:53.58,00:06:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat from the sun arrives \Nat the equator and is \Ncarried north by the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:57.92,00:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But global warming \Nis melting the polar ice caps \Nand disrupting this flow.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:03.76,00:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, \Nit will shut down.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:05.88,00:07:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that occurs, \Nthere goes \Nour warm climate.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:09.59,00:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. \NWhen do you think this \Ncould happen, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:14.39,00:07:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When? \NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:16.27,00:07:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe in a hundred years. \NMaybe in a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:18.27,00:07:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I do know is \Nthat if we do not act soon,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:21.23,00:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it is our children \Nand our grandchildren \Nwho will have to pay the price.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:26.82,00:07:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's going to pay \Nthe price of the Kyoto Accord?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:29.87,00:07:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It would cost \Nthe world's economy hundreds \Nof billions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:33.95,00:07:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect, \NMr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:36.45,00:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the cost of doing nothing \Ncould be even higher.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:39.58,00:07:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our climate is fragile.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:42.25,00:07:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At the rate we're burning \Nfossil fuels and polluting \Nthe environment,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:45.17,00:07:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the ice caps \Nwill soon disappear.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:47.80,00:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor, um, Hall,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:51.34,00:07:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,our economy is every bit \Nas fragile as the environment.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:54.64,00:07:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you should keep that \Nin mind before making \Nsensationalist claims.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:58.85,00:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the last chunk of ice \Nthat broke off...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:02.48,00:08:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was about the size \Nof the state of Rhode Island.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:04.90,00:08:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people might call that \Npretty sensational.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:07.78,00:08:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Men Chuckling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:08:11.20,00:08:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ People Shouting ] \NStop global warming!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:13.41,00:08:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NI'm here at the Global Warming \NConference in New Delhi,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:16.87,00:08:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where, if you can believe \Nyour eyes, it's snowing.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:19.16,00:08:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The coldest weather \Non record...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:21.50,00:08:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has thrown the city \Ninto chaos with numbers \Nof homeless people--
Dialogue: 0,00:08:24.75,00:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Taxi! Taxi!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:27.76,00:08:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoyed \Nyour testimony, Professor. \NIt was very spirited.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:31.68,00:08:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you. \NIt's what we're here for, \Nright? Put on a good show?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:35.35,00:08:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite. Uh, \NI was wondering if \NI could talk to you...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:38.81,00:08:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,about your theory \Non abrupt climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:41.56,00:08:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The name's Rapson. \NTerry Rapson.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:43.77,00:08:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Rapson? \NOf the Hedland Center? \NThat's me.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:47.15,00:08:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read your work \Non ocean currents.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:50.11,00:08:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say \Nto a spot of tea? \NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:52.53,00:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can hail a cab. \NOh.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:54.70,00:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Loud Whistle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:08:57.66,00:09:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,00:09:00.12,00:09:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ] \N[ Bell Clanging ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:17.47,00:09:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] Welcome back \Nto Glasgow, Scotland, \N[ Beeping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:19.60,00:09:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We return \Nto the action 63 minutes \Ninto the second half...
Dialogue: 0,00:09:30.19,00:09:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Dennis, NOMAD buoy 4311 \Nis showing a temperature drop...
Dialogue: 0,00:09:34.07,00:09:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of 13 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:36.70,00:09:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmm? Where is 4311? \N- Well, it's, uh,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:43.83,00:09:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Georges Bank. \N- Oh, it's rough seas out there. \NMust've knocked it about.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:51.05,00:09:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sheep Bleating ] \N[ Gulls Squawking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:57.72,00:09:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Television Chatter Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:59.72,00:10:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ] \N[ Announcement In Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:00.56,00:10:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Announcement Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:11.36,00:10:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Sirens Chirping ] \N- [ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:16.49,00:10:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cell Phone Ringing ] \N[ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:21.54,00:10:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman On Phone \NSpeaking Japanese ] \N[ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:27.71,00:10:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:45.02,00:10:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ People Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:11:10.09,00:11:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:11:22.01,00:11:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NParker, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:24.52,00:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We're seeing \Nsome bad weather \Nover Canaveral.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:27.52,00:11:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like \Nyou're coming back \Nthis week.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:29.69,00:11:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NYour wife's gonna \Ngive me an earful.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:31.77,00:11:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NRoger that.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:34.40,00:11:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man #2 ] \NHey, come take a look \Nat this storm system.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:36.65,00:11:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enormous.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:50.63,00:11:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:11:55.63,00:11:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:12:01.26,00:12:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe \NI'm spending two weeks \Nalone with my mum.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:03.56,00:12:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient with her, all right? \NShe's been looking forward \Nto this holiday for months.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:06.89,00:12:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. \N[ Both Chuckle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:12:08.89,00:12:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you. \NI love you too.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:15.07,00:12:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey, hello. \NBye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:19.49,00:12:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] The cause \Nof this extreme weather \Nremains a mystery,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:21.49,00:12:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,although some meteorologists \Nbelieve sunspots are to blame.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:26.04,00:12:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very odd.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:28.12,00:12:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a buoy here \Nregistering a 13 degree drop \Nin ocean temperature.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:32.25,00:12:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:34.29,00:12:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That buoy malfunctioned \Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:36.76,00:12:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll put a call in, \Nsee if there are any ships \Nnear Georges Bank to get it.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:39.72,00:12:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This buoy isn't \Nin Georges Bank. \NIt's just off Greenland.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:43.01,00:12:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:46.56,00:12:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the odds \Nof two buoys failing?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:48.98,00:12:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Remote.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:56.15,00:12:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Make that three.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:17.13,00:13:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:22.68,00:13:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Roaring ] \N- What's got into them?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:25.14,00:13:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Animals Howling, Calling ] \NI have no idea. \NThey're all worked up today.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:29.56,00:13:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:35.40,00:13:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:43.11,00:13:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it? \NTerry Rapson here. Sorry \Nto call you so early.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:48.16,00:13:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Professor. \NThat's all right. \NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:50.37,00:13:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've found \Nsomething extraordinary--
Dialogue: 0,00:13:53.83,00:13:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,extraordinary \Nand disturbing, \Nthat is.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:56.42,00:13:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You recall what you said \Nin New Delhi...
Dialogue: 0,00:13:58.59,00:14:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about how \Npolar melting might disrupt \Nthe North Atlantic current?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:02.30,00:14:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:04.22,00:14:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:06.09,00:14:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's happening.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:11.93,00:14:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? \NOne of our \NNOMAD buoys...
Dialogue: 0,00:14:14.73,00:14:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,registered a 13 degree drop \Nin surface temperature \Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:18.82,00:14:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent you \Nan e-mail. \NHold on.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:23.53,00:14:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At first we thought \Nit was a malfunction,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:26.16,00:14:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but there are four more \Nacross the North Atlantic \Nshowing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:30.41,00:14:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NThis is unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:32.83,00:14:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You predicted \Nit would happen.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:35.71,00:14:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but not \Nin our lifetime. \NThis is too fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:38.96,00:14:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no forecast models \Nremotely capable \Nof plotting this scenario,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:44.42,00:14:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,except yours.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:46.38,00:14:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My model is a reconstruction \Nof a prehistoric climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:49.55,00:14:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a forecast model. \NIt's the closest thing \Nwe have.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:54.18,00:14:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing like this \Nhas every happened before.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:58.02,00:15:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At least not in \Nthe last 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:27.18,00:15:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:28.43,00:15:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you be monitoring \Nthe weather or something?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:31.26,00:15:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is L.A. \NWhat weather?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:36.06,00:15:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Running, Faint ] \NWait. \NWhat's that noise?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:39.02,00:15:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What noise?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:41.94,00:15:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Running, Louder ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:46.15,00:15:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Stops ] \N[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:50.03,00:15:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NHoney, I'll be \Nright back.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:56.04,00:15:57.100,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NThe coast guard has \Nclosed the beaches...
Dialogue: 0,00:15:58.04,00:16:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as waves have been too big \Nfor even the most experienced \Nof surfers.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:00.42,00:16:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,L.A. Weather Center. \NIt's Tommy! \NI'm down at the beach!
Dialogue: 0,00:16:02.71,00:16:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle \Nof something. \NWhat do you need?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:04.80,00:16:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There-- Ooh! Uh.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:07.76,00:16:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's-- There's hail \Nthe size of golf balls \Ncoming down here!
Dialogue: 0,00:16:10.84,00:16:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Tommy Continues, Indistinct ] \N[ Man ] Low pressure system \Nmoving along...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:12.89,00:16:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the California coastline \Nis creating a cyclonic system \Nacross the L.A. basin.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:16.35,00:16:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:16:23.52,00:16:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hello. \NHey, boss, turn on \Nthe Weather Channel.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:26.19,00:16:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we have to issue \Na tornado warning.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:28.19,00:16:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What are \Nyou talking about?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:30.91,00:16:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NPalmdale and Lancaster \Nare reporting...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:32.91,00:16:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,wind speeds in excess \Nof 70 miles per hour, \NHold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:35.45,00:16:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions that are \Nhighly unusual for California.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:00.27,00:17:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NWe have live coverage now \Nfrom our Fox 11 chopper.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:03.69,00:17:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you there, Bart? \NUh, yes, I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:06.36,00:17:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,These tornadoes are forming \Nso fast-- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:09.53,00:17:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NOh! Oh, my God! \NLisa--
Dialogue: 0,00:17:12.74,00:17:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you getting this on camera? \NThis tornado just came \Nand erased the Hollywood sign.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:16.49,00:17:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hollywood sign is gone. \NIt's just shredded.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:20.20,00:17:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Roaring ] \N[ People Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:17:32.09,00:17:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Lisa ] \NBart, what can you see? \NIs anyone hurt?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:34.47,00:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NI wouldn't be surprised. There \Nis so much damage down there.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:37.22,00:17:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are people \Ndown there taking pictures!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:40.14,00:17:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What the hell \Nare you guys doing!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:42.39,00:17:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for cover! \NYou can't stay here! \NGet outta here!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:48.61,00:17:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're seeing are two \Nactual tornadoes striking Los \NAngeles International Airport.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:53.74,00:17:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Wait. It looks like \Nthey've joined and formed \None large tornado.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:56.99,00:18:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tommy! \NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:02.41,00:18:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NUrge all of our viewers to stay \Naway from the area.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:05.37,00:18:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jeff, where are you? \N- I'm on, uh, Yucca and Vine. \NI'm on my way in now.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:10.34,00:18:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeff, you're on TV! \NYou're right \Nin the middle of it!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:12.34,00:18:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:21.93,00:18:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta get \Nout of there, man!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:24.19,00:18:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:28.77,00:18:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NThat bus just got dropped \Non top of that Porsche!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:30.73,00:18:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Line Busy Tone ] \NOh, my God. I hope \Nno one was in that car!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:34.61,00:18:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NAnd for our national audience \Njust joining us now,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:36.66,00:18:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going live \Nto downtown Los Angeles \Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:38.87,00:18:42.100,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tommy? \N- If you look over there \Nbehind me, that's a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:43.08,00:18:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! A twister \Nin Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:45.71,00:18:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the many \Ntornadoes that are \Ndestroying our city.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:50.13,00:18:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one! \NThat's the Los Angeles \Nskyline!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:53.63,00:18:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable! \NIt's huge! I've never \Nseen anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:58.43,00:19:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:19:08.81,00:19:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,00:19:27.92,00:19:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rumbling Stops ]
Dialogue: 0,00:19:45.02,00:19:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:19:55.40,00:19:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Car Alarms Blaring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:20:17.59,00:20:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:20:21.26,00:20:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. All right. \NListen up, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:23.64,00:20:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, please. \NWe've got a lot of work to do \Nand we don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:27.81,00:20:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's get started, \Nplease. Vorsteen?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:32.02,00:20:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All our grid models \Nare worthless.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:34.65,00:20:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think grid models \Nare gonna be a lot of help here.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:36.90,00:20:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Canadians are reporting \Ntremendous circulation \Nmoving down from the Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:40.70,00:20:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In Siberia, there's \Na low pressure system \Nunlike anything we've seen,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:44.08,00:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and Australia just saw \Nthe strongest typhoon \Never recorded.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:46.99,00:20:49.100,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NHang on. Are you saying that \Nthese things are interconnected?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:50.08,00:20:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Booker ] \NWe have to consider \Nthe possibility.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:51.92,00:20:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The only force strong enough \Nto affect global weather \Nis the sun.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:54.92,00:20:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's NASA have to say? \N- We've already checked. \NSolar output is normal.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:59.84,00:21:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What about \Nthe North Atlantic current? \N[ Vorsteen ] What about it?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:04.97,00:21:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a call last night \Nfrom Professor Rapson \Nat the Hedland Center.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:08.93,00:21:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks the current \Nhas changed.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:10.85,00:21:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:21:12.98,00:21:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Jack. \NHow could that be?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:15.36,00:21:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The current depends upon \Na delicate balance of salt \Nand fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:18.23,00:21:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- We all know that. \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:21.74,00:21:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one has \Ntaken into account...
Dialogue: 0,00:21:23.82,00:21:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how much fresh water \Nhas been dumped into the ocean \Nbecause of melting polar ice.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:28.24,00:21:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we've hit \Na critical desalinization point.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:30.100,00:21:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:21:34.79,00:21:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It would explain \Nwhat's driving \Nthis extreme weather.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:37.09,00:21:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hedland had some pretty \Nconvincing data.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:40.05,00:21:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They've asked me to feed it into \Nmy paleoclimate model to track \Nthe next set of events.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:44.09,00:21:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Jack. Are you \Nsuggesting these weather \Nanomalies are gonna continue?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:47.93,00:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just continue-- \Nget worse.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:55.10,00:21:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we're on the verge \Nof a major climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:57.69,00:22:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:22:02.61,00:22:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom! \NWhat are you gonna tell \Nthe administration?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:05.87,00:22:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect me \Nto tell them?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:07.78,00:22:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The government has \Nto start making long-term \Npreparations now.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:10.66,00:22:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, all you have is a theory. \NThen give me the mainframe \Nand let me prove it!
Dialogue: 0,00:22:13.62,00:22:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:17.79,00:22:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:19.84,00:22:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NProfessor Hall.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:21.92,00:22:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? \NI think your theory \Nmay be correct.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:24.38,00:22:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk with me.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:26.01,00:22:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few weeks ago, \NI monitored the strongest \Nhurricane on record.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:29.97,00:22:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The hail, the tornadoes-- \Nit all fits.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:32.64,00:22:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the model \Nyou're working on \Nfactor in storm scenarios?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:35.31,00:22:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we haven't had \Nthe time. \NMaybe I can help.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:38.90,00:22:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome aboard. \NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:46.66,00:22:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack. Jack. \NWe got the results.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:58.79,00:23:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Six to eight months. \NThat can't be.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:01.13,00:23:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That time scale \Nisn't in months. \NIt's in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:08.55,00:23:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, the terrible weather \Nhasn't hit the D.C. area,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:10.47,00:23:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but local residents \Naren't taking any chances,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:13.22,00:23:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as people stock up \Nfor what is already \Nbeing billed...
Dialogue: 0,00:23:15.89,00:23:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as the worst storm season \Non record.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:18.65,00:23:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You better be sure \Nabout this, Jack. \NMy ass is on the line.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:21.15,00:23:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the model. \NAnd I hope to God \Nit's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:24.32,00:23:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. \NMr. Vice President. \NTom.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:26.74,00:23:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know \NProfessor Hall. \NYes, we've met.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:29.53,00:23:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Professor Hall has some \Nnew information I think \Nyou should take a look at.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:33.08,00:23:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We just got these results \Nfrom our simulation model.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:35.96,00:23:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They explain what's causing \Nthe severe weather.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:38.12,00:23:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look at this later. \NI have a meeting with \Nthe director of FEMA now.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:41.75,00:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very urgent, sir. \NOur climate \Nis changing violently.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:44.63,00:23:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to happen \Nover the next six \Nto eight weeks.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:47.30,00:23:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said this \Nwouldn't happen for another \Nhundred years or so.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:50.14,00:23:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong. \NWell, suppose \Nyou're wrong this time.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:52.76,00:23:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that I were, but I'm sure \Nthat you're aware of what's \Nhappening all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:56.77,00:24:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're making all the necessary \Npreparations for this storm. \NWhat more do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:00.35,00:24:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to start \Nthinking about large scale \Nevacuations right now,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:04.36,00:24:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in \Nthe northern states.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:06.40,00:24:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuations? \NYes.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:08.53,00:24:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you lost \Nyour mind, Hall? \NI have to go.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:12.41,00:24:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vice President, \Nif we don't act now, \Nit's going to be too late.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:21.25,00:24:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:26.01,00:24:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NIt's been 24 hours now since \Nthe snow started falling...
Dialogue: 0,00:24:29.38,00:24:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,across the British Isles \Nand over northern Europe,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:31.39,00:24:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and it shows no signs \Nof letting up.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:33.55,00:24:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No, no, no. \NYou gotta stop worrying. \NNo.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:36.22,00:24:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. We got plenty \Nof supplies with us. \NWe're just snowed in.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:40.35,00:24:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No, it's all right. \NIt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:43.40,00:24:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay \Nwhere you are, okay? \NI'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:45.40,00:24:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I love you too. \NOkay. Bye. \N[ Sighs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:24:49.28,00:24:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey. How's Jeanette? \N- Oh, fine.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:53.91,00:24:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ferry just landed. \NMust be nice in Spain. \NI wish I was there.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:58.100,00:25:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ TV: Reporter ] \NThe search and rescue team has \Nbeen deployed by helicopter...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:01.67,00:25:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to airlift \Nthe royal family to safety.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:04.59,00:25:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You think \Nthey'll come get us, \Nsince we got snowed in?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:06.75,00:25:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Not likely.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:09.26,00:25:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, \Nwe got our own genny,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:11.26,00:25:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,enough tea and biscuits \Nto sink a ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:13.80,00:25:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we'll be fine. \NAs long as the loo \Ndoesn't back up again.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:17.43,00:25:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Chuckle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:25:22.27,00:25:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In Ireland, those remaining \Nin Belfast and Banbridge \Nhave been urged to evacuate...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:26.61,00:25:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to Dublin as soon \Nas possible.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:29.86,00:25:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The north continues \Nto receive the worst \Nof the storm--
Dialogue: 0,00:25:33.99,00:25:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Helicopter Approaching ]
Dialogue: 0,00:25:38.49,00:25:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWe've got zero visibility. \NMaintain heading and speed.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:41.83,00:25:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Man #2 ] \NWhat's our heading? \N- Zero, three, five, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:44.25,00:25:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately 40 kilometers \Nfrom Balmoral Castle.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:47.50,00:25:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWe've lost visual contact \Nwith you.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:13.65,00:26:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This gauge here \Ncan't be right.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:15.70,00:26:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man #3 ] \NWind speed has dropped to zero.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:17.74,00:26:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have vertical walls \Nof cirrus cloud formations.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:20.33,00:26:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWhat the hell \Nis going on?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:21.87,00:26:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloody fuel lines \Nare starting to freeze!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:28.34,00:26:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Men Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:26:35.05,00:26:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Port engine pressure's dropping! \NThe rotor R.P.M. is dropping!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:39.05,00:26:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a flame-out \Non the starboard side as well!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:45.69,00:26:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare \Nfor crash landing!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:49.36,00:26:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Select emergency fuel!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:52.40,00:26:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, \Nyou bastard!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:55.11,00:26:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,00:27:10.79,00:27:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Breathing Heavily ]
Dialogue: 0,00:27:20.26,00:27:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson ] \NWhat I'm about to tell you \Nis supposed to be confidential.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:23.22,00:27:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Several hours ago, \Nthree helicopters went down \Nover Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:27.14,00:27:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They crashed because the fuel \Nin their lines froze.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:30.73,00:27:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,At what temperature does--
Dialogue: 0,00:27:32.69,00:27:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson On Speaker ] \NNegative 150 degrees Fahrenheit. \NWe had to look it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:37.91,00:27:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperature dropped \Nphenomenally fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:40.24,00:27:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,On the ground, people froze \Nbefore they could \Nget out of their cars.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:43.62,00:27:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get me a satellite picture \Nof Scotland two hours ago. \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:47.75,00:27:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got mountains of data \Nbut nowhere near enough \Ncomputer power to analyze it.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:52.25,00:27:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can you help us? \N- Send us what you've got, \Nand we'll do our best.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:55.67,00:27:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson ] \NThanks, Jack. Bye for now.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:59.30,00:28:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Scotland at the time \Nthe temperature dropped.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:05.10,00:28:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Frank ] \NThis thing looks \Njust like a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:07.94,00:28:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Janet ] \NOnly hurricanes don't form \Nover land.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:11.98,00:28:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mob scene here \Nat Grand Central Station.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:14.44,00:28:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Over half the platforms \Nare flooded,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:16.74,00:28:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and service has been \Nsuspended on all trains.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:19.66,00:28:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With planes still grounded \Nand trains now out of service, \Nthat's bad news--
Dialogue: 0,00:28:24.24,00:28:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor's coming to pick me up. \NDo you guys want a ride \Nto the train station?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:27.96,00:28:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Stranded \Nsince this morning. \NNot anymore.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:31.17,00:28:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In Nova Scotia earlier, \Nthe ocean rose by 25 feet \Nin a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:35.67,00:28:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have feared \Nfor the past few days \Nhas indeed happened.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:40.01,00:28:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The cold front moving down \Nfrom the Arctic...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:42.26,00:28:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,has created an enormous \Nstorm system in Canada,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:45.18,00:28:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which, incredible as it sounds, \Nlooks like a tropical hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:48.60,00:28:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta go pick up \Nmy little brother. \NDo you guys want a ride?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:52.19,00:28:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he? \NHe's in a boarding school \Nin Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:55.52,00:29:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If this system moves south, \Nwe could see a wind-driven \Nstorm surge...
Dialogue: 0,00:29:00.45,00:29:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that could threaten \Nthe entire Eastern Seaboard.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:03.78,00:29:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Bye. Victor's stuck \Nin traffic on Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:07.95,00:29:10.100,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be easier \Nto head out of town \Nif we meet him over there.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:11.04,00:29:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. \NYou mean walk? \NNo, not in this.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:15.42,00:29:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:18.01,00:29:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We should take \Nthe stairs.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:20.47,00:29:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on the top floor.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:25.35,00:29:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we're walkin'.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:29.64,00:29:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:31.94,00:29:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Horns Honking, \NPeople Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:39.57,00:29:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should just stay here. \NI think the young lady \Nis right, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:43.99,00:29:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We need to get home.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:46.95,00:29:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! \N[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:59.63,00:30:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Goats Bleating ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:05.39,00:30:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growls ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:11.60,00:30:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Cesar, come here.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:13.81,00:30:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:20.65,00:30:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolves! \NThey're gone!
Dialogue: 0,00:30:23.61,00:30:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NJust to give you an idea \Nof the situation,
Dialogue: 0,00:30:26.28,00:30:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems to be becoming \Nworse with each passing minute,
Dialogue: 0,00:30:29.45,00:30:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment, we have flooding \Nin most parts of the island.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:33.54,00:30:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got traffic snarl-ups \Nbecause the electricity \Nis now out...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:36.58,00:30:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to almost every part \Nof Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:39.55,00:30:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No traffic signals, \Ncar accidents-- at least 200--
Dialogue: 0,00:30:43.13,00:30:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and Lower Manhattan, we've been \Ntold, is virtually inaccessible.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:47.34,00:30:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NNo one is to be on the streets. \NPlease go inside.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:51.93,00:30:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Excited Chattering ] \NSir, just calm down.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:57.19,00:30:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Public library's right up here. \NMake your way up there. \NYou can stay warm and dry.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:00.07,00:31:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. \NThis way.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:02.73,00:31:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. \NYour bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:05.15,00:31:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn $1,500 \Nwaterproof raincoat!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:08.16,00:31:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please shut up, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.12,00:31:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be rats \Neverywhere. \NThat's 'cause it's New York.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:12.100,00:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! \NOpen up, big poppa!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:17.12,00:31:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of service. \NIt's out of service!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:20.88,00:31:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. I'll give you \N$100 to put it in service. \NYou don't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:23.84,00:31:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. Really, $200. \NI won't have it. \NI won't have it.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:27.34,00:31:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I love buses. \NThis is just so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:30.18,00:31:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting ] \NHello?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:32.76,00:31:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't reach my driver. \NI lost the signal.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:35.48,00:31:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is insane. \NWe should just go back \Nto your apartment.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:38.19,00:31:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Brian ] \NYeah. I vote for that.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:40.19,00:31:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Are you kidding? \NWe have to get higher!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:42.86,00:31:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. \NUp to the library.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:45.69,00:31:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:10.47,00:32:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:14.56,00:32:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Child Screams ] \N- [ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:34.62,00:32:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NThere is a wall of water \Ncoming towards New York City!
Dialogue: 0,00:32:37.96,00:32:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody--
Dialogue: 0,00:32:41.17,00:32:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting, Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:47.46,00:32:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Woman Screams ] \N- [ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:33:25.84,00:33:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my--
Dialogue: 0,00:33:33.93,00:33:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:40.93,00:33:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:43.44,00:33:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No! \NNo, Sam! Sam, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:45.36,00:33:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura! Laura! Laura! \NCome on! \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,00:33:49.61,00:33:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:54.20,00:33:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam! \N- Go!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:15.26,00:34:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Dog Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:34:33.70,00:34:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here he is.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:37.74,00:34:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, were you able \Nto re-create the thermal cycle?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:41.66,00:34:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The storm's rotation \Nis pulling super-cooled air \Ndown from the upper troposphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:50.00,00:34:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But shouldn't the air warm up \Nbefore it reaches ground level?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:54.05,00:34:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It should, but it doesn't. \NThe air's descending \Ntoo rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:58.64,00:35:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this \Nan isolated incident?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:04.23,00:35:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:06.27,00:35:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We've located two other \Nsupercells in addition \Nto the one over Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:10.07,00:35:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one over Northern Canada \Nand another one over Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:14.40,00:35:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And do we know \Ntheir projected path?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:18.03,00:35:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Our previous estimates \Nof six to eight weeks \Nweren't even close.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:22.62,00:35:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This one storm is going \Nto change the face \Nof our planet.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:26.33,00:35:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a projection \Nof 24 hours out.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:34.42,00:35:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 48 hours out.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:39.30,00:35:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And in seven to 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:45.14,00:35:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When this storm is over, \Nwe'll be in a new ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:54.15,00:35:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:14.46,00:36:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor, it's time \Nyou got out of there.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:20.22,00:36:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that time \Nhas come and gone, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:28.48,00:36:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,00:36:34.07,00:36:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Save as many as you can.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:36.69,00:36:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Feedback On Line ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:41.70,00:36:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Disconnect Signal ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:47.45,00:36:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:51.67,00:36:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack. Something's \Nhappened in New York.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:05.85,00:37:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No. The power is out. \NI've been in here all day.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:09.14,00:37:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NWho needs help? \NOver here. Over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:12.40,00:37:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Indistinct Shouting ] \NHi.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:14.90,00:37:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NHello. \N[ Dog Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:37:18.94,00:37:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:21.61,00:37:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last one. \NEnjoy it. Greedy.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:26.70,00:37:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Operator ] \NAll circuits are busy.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:29.25,00:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Dialing Phone ]
Dialogue: 0,00:37:31.08,00:37:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you reach \Nyour little brother yet?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:33.83,00:37:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There's still no service. \NDamn cell phones.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:41.93,00:37:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:44.05,00:37:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any pay phones \Non the upper floors? \NNo. No.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:46.89,00:37:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some \Non the mezzanine. \NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:49.72,00:37:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- But I think it's underwater. \N- Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:52.19,00:37:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The power's out. \NOlder pay phones draw their \Npower directly from the line.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:56.19,00:37:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman On P.A., Indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:37:58.82,00:38:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God. I've been trying \Nto reach Sam.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:02.57,00:38:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So have I. \NI kept trying to call you, \Nbut I couldn't get through.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:06.87,00:38:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a madhouse \Naround here. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:14.42,00:38:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:19.71,00:38:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:24.59,00:38:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Dial Tone ] \N- It works.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:28.22,00:38:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack? Sam's on the phone. \NLine four.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:32.81,00:38:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam? \N- Dad!
Dialogue: 0,00:38:35.44,00:38:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you? \NAre you all right? \NWe're at the public library.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:38.52,00:38:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam, it's Mom. \NI'm so happy you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:42.53,00:38:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, can you call \NLaura and Brian's parents \Nand tell them we're all right?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:47.28,00:38:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:49.62,00:38:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam, what's that noise? \N- Sam? Sam?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:53.41,00:38:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ] \NWhat is going on out there, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:58.54,00:39:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam? Sam, listen to me. \NListen very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:02.71,00:39:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget what I said \Nabout trying to head south.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:05.43,00:39:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late for that. \NThe storm is just gonna \Nget worse.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:08.47,00:39:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna turn into \Na massive blizzard with an eye \Nin the center, like a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:12.64,00:39:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh-huh. \N- The air is gonna be so cold,
Dialogue: 0,00:39:15.44,00:39:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you could freeze to death \Nin seconds.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:20.36,00:39:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam? \N- What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:23.74,00:39:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, son. \NDo not go outside.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:26.99,00:39:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just burn whatever you can \Nto stay warm and try \Nto wait it out.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:30.78,00:39:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I will come for you. \NDo you understand me? \NI will come for you.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:34.20,00:39:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shivering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:39:36.71,00:39:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam! Sam, come back!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:40.71,00:39:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NSam? Sam, did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:43.96,00:39:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:05.44,00:40:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:40:08.78,00:40:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shivering, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:40:11.28,00:40:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sobbing ] \NI thought you drowned.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:19.12,00:40:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's find some \Ndry clothes for you. \NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:28.76,00:40:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you store \Nthe arctic gear?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:31.72,00:40:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make it \Nto New York, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:34.14,00:40:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've walked that far \Nbefore in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:37.06,00:40:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the same. \NJack, this is not the same!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:41.65,00:40:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy, tell him.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:45.32,00:40:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do this.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:49.65,00:40:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:57.66,00:41:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank told me about Sam.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:00.25,00:41:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna try \Nto talk you out of going,
Dialogue: 0,00:41:02.67,00:41:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's something \NI need for you to do first.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:05.55,00:41:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to explain your results \Nto the administration.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:08.34,00:41:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I already tried that. \NI know this time \Nwill be different.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:10.47,00:41:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna brief \Nthe president directly.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:15.93,00:41:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NIs that the last of it?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:17.93,00:41:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laura ] \NYeah. Pretty much. \NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:20.60,00:41:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We also found this radio, \Nbut I don't think it works.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:23.19,00:41:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see it.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:25.94,00:41:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:41:30.99,00:41:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha, be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,00:41:33.62,00:41:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You ain't even supposed \Nto be in here anyway.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:37.29,00:41:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Barking Continues ] \N- [ Loud Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:41:47.30,00:41:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rumbling Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:42:20.70,00:42:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:42:31.84,00:42:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:40.14,00:42:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:51.78,00:42:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Shattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:43:04.79,00:43:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic rule of storms \Nis that they continue...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:07.67,00:43:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,until the imbalance \Nthat created them is corrected.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:10.84,00:43:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we're talking \Nabout a global realignment.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:14.59,00:43:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The superstorm will \Nlast seven to 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:18.01,00:43:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's over, ice and snow \Nwill cover the entire \NNorthern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:23.22,00:43:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The ice and snow \Nwill reflect sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:26.81,00:43:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth's atmosphere \Nwill restabilize...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:29.02,00:43:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but with an average \Ntemperature close to that \Nof the last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:33.78,00:43:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do about this?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:35.74,00:43:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NHead as far south as possible.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:39.24,00:43:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not amusing, \NProfessor.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:41.53,00:43:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you suggest \Nthey go?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:44.25,00:43:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The farther south they go, \Nthe safer they'll be.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:47.12,00:43:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Texas. Parts of Florida \Nthat aren't flooded. \NMexico would be best.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:51.29,00:43:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico? Maybe \Nyou should stick to science \Nand leave policy to us.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:55.47,00:43:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we tried that approach. \NYou didn't want to hear \Nabout the science...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:58.76,00:44:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when it could \Nhave made a difference.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:02.22,00:44:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly are you \Nproposing, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:11.36,00:44:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate everyone \Nsouth of that line.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:20.49,00:44:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the people \Nin the north?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:26.75,00:44:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid \Nit's too late for them.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:29.54,00:44:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If they go outside, \Nthe storm will kill them.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:36.96,00:44:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:39.63,00:44:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,their best chance \Nis to stay inside,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:42.89,00:44:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,try to ride it out,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:46.27,00:44:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,pray.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:52.36,00:44:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think he'll do?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:55.11,00:44:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:57.32,00:45:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:00.28,00:45:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And good luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:02.28,00:45:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You too.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:06.08,00:45:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all gonna need it.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:10.83,00:45:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:45:16.00,00:45:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Generator Chugging ]
Dialogue: 0,00:45:27.89,00:45:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, mates, but we're \Njust about out of petrol.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:34.73,00:45:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there any chance...
Dialogue: 0,00:45:38.44,00:45:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will run... on this?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:42.61,00:45:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NAre you mad?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:45.45,00:45:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a 12-year-old scotch.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:55.46,00:45:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:46:09.68,00:46:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen. To England.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:15.27,00:46:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To mankind.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:18.69,00:46:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To Manchester United.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:20.94,00:46:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Laughing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:46:45.93,00:46:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Buddha. Come on. \NDo your business.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:49.47,00:46:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. There's nobody around.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:52.39,00:46:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Whimpering ] \NOkay. You know what? \NI'll turn around. I won't look.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:55.56,00:46:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise. \N[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:46:58.15,00:47:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking Continues ] \NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:08.16,00:47:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, man. \NThere's people out there. \NI was walking my dog.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:11.83,00:47:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's hundreds of 'em. \NThey're walkin' on the snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:19.38,00:47:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:47:23.67,00:47:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NWhere are they all going?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:25.68,00:47:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gettin' \Nout of the city \Nbefore it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:31.31,00:47:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:47:59.63,00:48:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:01.63,00:48:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be \Non a bus heading south.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:05.13,00:48:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been watching \Nyour back for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:07.97,00:48:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'd let you \Ngo alone?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:10.47,00:48:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All these years, I thought \NI was watching your back.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:13.43,00:48:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the keys? \NIn the truck.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:17.14,00:48:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think \Nyou're going?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:19.65,00:48:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither one of you \Nknows how to navigate \Nworth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:22.52,00:48:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Without me, you'll \Nend up in Cleveland.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:26.65,00:48:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to give you \Nupdates on the storm \Nas it heads your way.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:30.16,00:48:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:32.91,00:48:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Engine Starts ]
Dialogue: 0,00:48:45.96,00:48:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Reporting ] \NBreaking news from \Nthe U.S.-Mexico border.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:49.01,00:48:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just half an hour ago, \NMexican officials \Nclosed the border...
Dialogue: 0,00:48:52.51,00:48:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in the light \Nof so many U.S. refugees \Nwho are fleeing south...
Dialogue: 0,00:48:56.47,00:48:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the wake \Nof the approaching storm.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:58.85,00:49:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These people came here \Nin anticipation of crossing \Ninto Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:02.48,00:49:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they've been met \Nwith closed gates--
Dialogue: 0,00:49:05.40,00:49:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:07.44,00:49:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this fireplace \Nprobably hasn't been used \Nin about a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:14.99,00:49:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:22.38,00:49:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- What do you think \Nwe were gonna burn?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:25.96,00:49:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't burn books. \NNo. Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:29.55,00:49:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna freeze to death?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:34.22,00:49:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go get some more. \NI'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:38.31,00:49:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going with them.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:41.73,00:49:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Do you have \Na cafeteria or a lunchroom?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:45.02,00:49:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just an employees' lounge \Nwith a few vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:47.57,00:49:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:49:55.32,00:49:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna last very long \Non M&M's and potato chips.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:57.99,00:50:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the garbage cans? \NThere's always somethin' \Nto eat in the garbage.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:01.87,00:50:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:50:11.88,00:50:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasps ] \NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:14.68,00:50:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm fine. I just \Ncut my leg the other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:17.81,00:50:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Radio Static ]
Dialogue: 0,00:50:21.23,00:50:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get a signal?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:23.81,00:50:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. For a minute. \NAnd?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:30.86,00:50:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this storm is everywhere. \NIt's hit the entire \NNorthern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:35.61,00:50:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe is buried \Nunder 15 feet of snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:39.33,00:50:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say it's gonna \Nget just as bad here.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:41.79,00:50:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't think \Nyour dad's gonna make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:48.71,00:50:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:54.93,00:50:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:00.77,00:51:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NThe White House has ordered...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:02.81,00:51:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the following national disaster \Nalert for all northern states:
Dialogue: 0,00:51:06.60,00:51:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Continued exposure \Nto the approaching storm \Nis deadly.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:09.73,00:51:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Remain indoors and take \Nall measures to stay warm,
Dialogue: 0,00:51:12.07,00:51:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,burning any fuel sources \Nuntil the storm is over.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:15.49,00:51:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Roads are impassable \Nacross New York State...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:17.87,00:51:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and as far south \Nas Pennsylvania. \NWhere are we?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:20.62,00:51:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News Continues, \NIndistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:51:23.25,00:51:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're \Njust north of Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:26.62,00:51:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NRescue workers say \Nthey have no idea--
Dialogue: 0,00:51:29.75,00:51:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,00:51:34.13,00:51:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:36.88,00:51:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:44.77,00:51:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Once again, roads across \Nthe northern states... \N- Sorry, boss.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:48.19,00:51:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are impassable. \NUnpack the snowshoes. \NWe're walking from here.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:54.65,00:51:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, men. \NLet's get up and get going.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:57.95,00:52:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We've only made it to Brooklyn. \NMaybe we should just turn back.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:03.29,00:52:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What for? Half the city's \Nfrozen underwater.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:05.96,00:52:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to go back to. \NIt's time to get up. \NKeep moving.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:08.79,00:52:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We should've stayed \Nin the library. \NCome on, men.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:12.46,00:52:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, guys. \NLet's get moving.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:24.68,00:52:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:44.37,00:52:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? \NInsulatin'.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:48.33,00:52:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Newspaper's best, \Nbut this'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:50.96,00:52:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you spend \Nsome years on the streets, \Nand you learn how to keep warm.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:55.00,00:52:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:01.39,00:53:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:42.76,00:53:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:53:58.94,00:54:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groaning, Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:54:07.83,00:54:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NFrank!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:09.87,00:54:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right? \NI'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:15.00,00:54:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just dropped in \Nto do a little shopping.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:17.75,00:54:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta lose this sled.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:37.44,00:54:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on! \NWe'll pull you up!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:41.94,00:54:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason! You gotta \Nsupport Frank's weight!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:45.28,00:54:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I'll try!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:50.24,00:54:51.100,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:54:54.12,00:54:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I think \NI have his weight now!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:57.25,00:54:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming to you!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:05.63,00:55:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Cracking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:55:08.01,00:55:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:55:10.97,00:55:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The glass is breaking!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:15.98,00:55:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much weight!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:21.78,00:55:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not gonna hold.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:32.87,00:55:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:34.54,00:55:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank! \NI can get you out!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:39.54,00:55:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NDon't do it!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:41.75,00:55:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- No! Frank! Don't! \N- Frank, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:45.72,00:55:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:29.84,00:56:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Radio: \NChatter, Indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:56:32.35,00:56:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Get this convoy \Nmoving now.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:36.77,00:56:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Whispering ] \NI know. I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:39.73,00:56:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President. \NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:42.52,00:56:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, sir. \NWe can't wait any longer.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:45.53,00:56:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the last ones.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:47.95,00:56:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:05.21,00:57:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Pilot ] \NMexicali Control, \Nthis is Delta 2-6.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:07.92,00:57:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're carrying an urgent message \Nfor high command.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:10.88,00:57:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Request priority \Non landing zone one.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:13.01,00:57:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering, Shouting ] \N[ Radio Chatter Continues, \NIndistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:57:21.27,00:57:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:23.40,00:57:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Corporal. \NCarry on.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:39.04,00:57:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Madam Secretary?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:50.42,00:57:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:52.80,00:57:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The president's motorcade \Ngot caught in the storm.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:00.18,00:58:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:07.94,00:58:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She wouldn't \Nwake up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:10.28,00:58:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I-- I mean, last night \Nshe only had a fever. \NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:13.70,00:58:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,God, she's awfully pale.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:15.66,00:58:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, guys, look. \Nnone of us has had anything \Nreal to eat in days.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:18.70,00:58:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jeremy ] I'm telling you, \Nit's hypothermia. \NHow could it be hypothermia?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:21.96,00:58:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all been-- \NMaybe it's just \Nthe flu, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:24.25,00:58:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, \Nit's not the flu.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:27.71,00:58:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? \NAnd how do you know?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:29.96,00:58:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Books can be good for \Nsomething other than burning. \NLet's go over her symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:33.43,00:58:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you. She has a fever \Nand a really cold sweat.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:36.97,00:58:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NHow's her pulse?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:39.14,00:58:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:41.02,00:58:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she have any injuries, \Nlike a cut or something \Nthat might have gotten infected?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:44.44,00:58:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She was complaining \Nabout a cut on her leg \Na few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:48.15,00:58:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't-- I didn't \Nthink anything of it.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:55.66,00:58:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gosh.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:58.70,00:59:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's blood poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:00.79,00:59:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, septicemia. \NShe could go into septic shock.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:04.46,00:59:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen that before. \NThat can get bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:06.71,00:59:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs a massive dose \Nof penicillin...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:08.84,00:59:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or a broad-spectrum \Nantibiotic immediately,
Dialogue: 0,00:59:11.13,00:59:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or--
Dialogue: 0,00:59:17.34,00:59:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:39.70,00:59:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen \Nanything like it. \NThere's no point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:42.100,00:59:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can see \Nis cloud cover.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:44.87,00:59:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:46.92,00:59:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking infrared image \Nof thermal currents...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:50.29,00:59:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sent to Houston, Korolev,
Dialogue: 0,00:59:52.80,00:59:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your weather service.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:54.84,00:59:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Parker ] \NI'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:57.88,00:59:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom? \NTom, wake up. \N[ Groans ]
Dialogue: 0,01:00:00.01,01:00:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just received \Nsome satellite images \Nfrom the space station.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:02.89,01:00:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better take a look.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:16.24,01:00:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How big is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:18.07,01:00:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The vortex is \N50 miles in diameter \Nand growing.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:21.03,01:00:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The two cells \Nover Europe and Asia \Nare even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:23.54,01:00:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Tom ] \NGood God.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:25.41,01:00:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's gonna hit New York \Ninside an hour.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:31.08,01:00:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping, Panting ] \NJack--
Dialogue: 0,01:00:44.51,01:00:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason!
Dialogue: 0,01:00:46.60,01:00:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:48.35,01:00:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason!
Dialogue: 0,01:00:54.94,01:00:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Panting, Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,01:00:59.78,01:01:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,01:01:06.45,01:01:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- There's gotta be medicine \Non that ship.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:09.96,01:01:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said \Nit was too dangerous \Nto go outside.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:12.63,01:01:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I did.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:20.93,01:01:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you find \Nthose chairs?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:34.52,01:01:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:02:21.28,01:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:23.91,01:02:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Lock Rattling ] \NOhh! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:26.58,01:02:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:28.79,01:02:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Grunts Loudly ] \N- [ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:02:35.75,01:02:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:00.90,01:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yells ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:06.07,01:03:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:16.33,01:03:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's all in Russian. I-- \N- [ Sam ] I know.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:19.09,01:03:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- H-H-Hey, guys, I found it. \N- What? How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:22.76,01:03:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it says "penicillin" \Non the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:25.47,01:03:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:30.60,01:03:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. This is the mess hall. \NWe should find some food \Nwhile we're here.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:34.52,01:03:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time. \NNone of us are gonna survive \Nwithout food, including Laura.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:39.61,01:03:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:43.44,01:03:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Exhales, Clears Throat ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:45.49,01:03:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. ] \NSam, over here!
Dialogue: 0,01:03:47.61,01:03:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:49.62,01:03:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Bingo. \N[ Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:51.79,01:03:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:53.87,01:03:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Clattering ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:58.75,01:04:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Inflating Loudly ] \N[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:02.30,01:04:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam ] \NBrian?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:04.46,01:04:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Brian ] \NI'm okay. \N[ J.D. ] What happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:07.18,01:04:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay. All I did \Nwas open up a cupboard.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:10.80,01:04:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Quiet Snarling ] \NWe can use it. \NPut food in it.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:14.02,01:04:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Loud Snarl ] \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:15.89,01:04:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling ] \N[ Panicked Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:22.19,01:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Continues Yelling ] \N- [ Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:26.61,01:04:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull him in! \N[ Wolf Whimpers ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:29.16,01:04:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Whimpering, Growling ] \NYou all right?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:36.50,01:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. Groans ] \NMy leg.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:41.84,01:04:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, use this.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:43.34,01:04:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shuddering, Groaning ] \NOh, yeah. Here. Ohh!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:51.72,01:04:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be \Nover New York by now.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:54.31,01:04:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Satellite readings \Nare showing a temperature drop \Nof 10 degrees per second.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:15.08,01:05:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam ] \NYou guys, I think \Nwe're in the eye of it.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:18.79,01:05:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta get back right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:23.04,01:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, \NI'm gonna go outside...
Dialogue: 0,01:05:24.96,01:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm gonna lure the wolves \Nout of the room.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:28.13,01:05:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- When they leave, \Nyou lock the door. \N- Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:02.67,01:06:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Crunch ] \N- [ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:06.63,01:06:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:09.26,01:06:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah! \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:12.30,01:06:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Muttering, Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:16.89,01:06:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling, Snarling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:20.73,01:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah! \N[ Panting, Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:29.19,01:06:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Wolf Whimpers ] \N- [ Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:35.57,01:06:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groans ] \NBrian, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:38.99,01:06:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Muttering ] \NCome on! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:43.37,01:06:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Snarling, Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:45.63,01:06:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groans, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:48.80,01:06:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling Continues ] \N[ Banging On Door ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:52.59,01:06:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian! \NBrian, open the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:59.31,01:07:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to get out of here now. \NBrian, get the supplies.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:42.06,01:07:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:07:53.57,01:07:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crackling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:08:01.24,01:08:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:02.91,01:08:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull! Pull, Brian!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:30.06,01:08:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Pull!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:40.87,01:08:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the medicine to Laura!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:43.08,01:08:45.100,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. Groaning, Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:09:14.48,01:09:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost there, man! \NCome on! Aah! \N[ Grunts ]
Dialogue: 0,01:09:18.19,01:09:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian, close the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:32.63,01:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let the fire \Ngo out!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:35.00,01:09:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:43.14,01:09:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha, \Ncome away from the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:46.60,01:09:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, Buddha, come!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:48.06,01:09:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,More books! More books!
Dialogue: 0,01:10:45.16,01:10:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How long \Nhave I been out of it?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:48.16,01:10:50.100,Default,,0,0,0,,Couple hours. \NHow do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:51.08,01:10:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:52.87,01:10:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:54.92,01:10:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we had to get inside \Nin kind of a hurry, \Nso I sort of pushed you in.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:00.76,01:11:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be used to \Nyou pushing me around.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:04.26,01:11:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to have you back.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:11.14,01:11:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:14.31,01:11:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The eye of the storm \Nhas passed,
Dialogue: 0,01:11:16.52,01:11:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're 40 miles \Nfrom Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:18.52,01:11:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we wait \None more day?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:23.28,01:11:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam may not have \None more day.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:37.19,01:12:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think's \Ngonna happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:41.11,01:12:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:44.19,01:12:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean us. \NCivilization.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:46.61,01:12:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:50.70,01:12:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind survived \Nthe last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:53.74,01:12:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We're certainly capable \Nof surviving this one.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:58.66,01:13:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All depends on \Nwhether or not we're able \Nto learn from our mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:04.63,01:13:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure as hell would like \Na chance to learn from mine.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:09.13,01:13:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You did everything you could.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:14.43,01:13:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about Sam.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:22.44,01:13:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, you know \Nthe chances of Sam--
Dialogue: 0,01:13:36.99,01:13:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I made my son a promise.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:40.79,01:13:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:05.77,01:14:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On Radio ] \NParker, this is Houston. \NDo you read?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:09.40,01:14:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger, Mission Control. \NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:11.45,01:14:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting scattered reports \Nthat the storm is dissipating \Nover North America.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:15.41,01:14:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you confirm?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:19.04,01:14:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Parker ] \NAffirmative. \NIt's finally clearing.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:23.42,01:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We're over Europe right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:25.46,01:14:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see landmass \Nfor the first time in days.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:17.53,01:16:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How much further is it \Nto the library?
Dialogue: 0,01:16:20.07,01:16:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be...
Dialogue: 0,01:16:25.45,01:16:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right here.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:31.92,01:16:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:11.21,01:17:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:21.28,01:18:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:30.16,01:18:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My father.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:35.92,01:18:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:42.43,01:18:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:10.24,01:19:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crowd Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:19:23.67,01:19:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,01:19:34.35,01:19:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:39.19,01:19:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I just received \Na shortwave radio transmission \Nfrom Jack Hall.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:43.15,01:19:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He made it to New York.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:45.61,01:19:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He says \Nthere are survivors.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:49.37,01:19:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:51.62,01:19:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's--
Dialogue: 0,01:19:54.62,01:19:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good news.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:30.53,01:20:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack! \NIt's good to see you!
Dialogue: 0,01:20:33.95,01:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. \NLet's go get on board.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:31.22,01:21:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:33.64,01:21:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:21:35.60,01:21:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen the air \Nso clear?
